- main issue directions investigated: reward scheduling vs global mint-cap backing; lifetime reward budget accounting under zero-stake / early-stop periods; stake ledger mismatch for fee-on-transfer or rebasing staking tokens; numeric truncation risk from `uint96 totalRewardsSupply`
- promising but not retained directions: auxiliary access/control and pause-related interfaces were reviewed for context (`RewardsDistributionRecipient.sol`, `Pausable.sol`, `Owned.sol`), but no separate retained issue came out of them in this round

## Cross-Agent Status
